KING FAN HAS READ THIS SCRIPT BEFORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I've suffered with the Kings, or they have caused me to suffer, since 1967. 
I've seen them make trade after trade, giving up draft choices or young talent 
one after another. 
</P>
<P>
Suddenly, there comes this expansion team called the New York Islanders whose 
general manager says that he is going to build his team around young talent and 
draft choices with patience. 
</P>
<P>
A few years later, they obtained the services of one of the most popular Kings 
ever, Butch Goring, on their way to four Stanley Cups. 
</P>
<P>
Now, in their 23rd year, the Kings again have traded away their draft choices 
and young talent, and the Islanders are again building like they did then, with 
a lot of patience. 
</P>
<P>
Guess who's going to win the Stanley Cup again long before the Kings are? You 
guessed it. 
</P>
<P>
