<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SLAYBACK'S 2 GOALS LEAD LAGUNA HILLS PAST BELL GARDENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brian Slayback scored two goals to lead Laguna Hills High School to a 4-0 
victory over Bell Gardens Friday in a Southern Section 2-A quarterfinal match 
at Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Slayback tied the Laguna Hills' single-season record of 23 set by Brian Fleming 
(1986-87). 
</P>
<P>
Chris Kannenberg and Scott Clark also scored. Chad Davidson had eight saves for 
his seventh shutout for Laguna Hills (22-5). 
</P>
<P>
In another 2-A boys' match: 
</P>
<P>
Orange 5, Montebello 1 -- Montebello (19-2-4) led, 1-0, when Jose Juarez scored 
10 minutes into the match. But Tim Huhn scored 15 minutes later and Ricky 
Heimer scored three goals in the second half as host Orange (18-0-4) pulled 
away. Juan Viveros also scored for Orange, the top seed in 2-A. . It was the 
third time that Heimer has scored three goals in a match this season. Orange's 
Tres Martin had five saves 
</P>
<P>
In the 4-A Division: 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley 1, Mater Dei 0 (OT) -- Tom Hamlin scored two minutes into the 
second 10-minute overtime to give the hosts the victory. Simi Valley improved 
its record to 27-1, while Mater Dei finished at 16-7-2. 
</P>
<P>
In the Small Schools Division: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran 1, Temecula Valley 0 -- Jason Haynes scored five minutes into 
the match to lead host Orange Lutheran (16-2-2). Dave Hopper had six saves for 
Orange Lutheran and Chris Snodgrass had 14 saves for Temecula Valley. 
</P>
