<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LEBANON; 
</P>
<P>
MORTAR DUELS KILL 3; TRUCE JEOPARDIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sniper fire escalated to mortar duels between Christian forces that killed at 
least three people, wounded 22 and jeopardized a six-day-old truce in East 
Beirut. 
</P>
<P>
It was the worst cease-fire violation since the truce went into effect. By 
police count, the battle for control of the Christian enclave between Samir 
Geagea's Lebanese Forces militia and the rival army troops of Maj. Gen. Michel 
Aoun has killed 688 people and wounded 1,906 since it broke out Jan. 30. Geagea 
had declared his war to be over, but Aoun said the existence of two military 
forces is not acceptable. 
</P>
