<P>
UNITED NATIONS; 
</P>
<P>
FAR-REACHING PLAN TO FIGHT DRUGS OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.N. General Assembly adopted by consensus a plan to tackle every phase of 
the international drug trade, from the cultivation of coca leaves and poppies 
to street-corner sales of cocaine and opium. The plan, which carries no 
immediate price tag, includes proposals for halting the smuggling of narcotics 
and the "laundering" of profits through the banking system, and for 
rehabilitating millions of addicts. 
</P>
