<P>
MUSLIM CLERIC CALLS FOR HOSTAGES' RELEASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheik Mohammed Hussein Fadlallah, the spiritual mentor of the Iranian-backed 
Hezbollah (Party of God), appealed for the release of 17 Western hostages in 
Lebanon, saying the West has used their plight to "disfigure the image of Islam 
and Muslims." The cleric may have been reacting to an editorial in Iran's 
pro-government Tehran Times, which said, "Regardless of the West's propaganda 
ploys, Muslim forces out of Islamic and humanitarian considerations should work 
to get hostages free with no precondition." 
</P>
