<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Viejo Bancorp: The holding company for Mission Viejo National Bank reported 
record net earnings of $2.3 million for 1989, 42% more than the $1.6 million 
for 1988. For the fourth quarter, net income rose 25%, to $636,000 from 
$507,000. Total assets reached $131.4 million, 62% more than the $80.9 million 
reported at the end of 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
