<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Standard Logic Inc.: The Anaheim-based electronics manufacturer said it lost 
$99,485 for the first quarter of fiscal 1990, contrasted with the net loss of 
$474,428 reported for the like period the previous year. Revenue for the 
quarter ended Jan. 27 declined 19%, to $187,850 from $232,595. The company said 
the first-quarter loss is a result of lower bookings and that it expects to 
report a profit for the third quarter. 
</P>
