<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UniCare Financial Corp.: The Irvine-based holding company for UniCare Insurance 
Co. reported net income of $2 million for the fourth quarter, up 17% from the 
$1.7 million reported for the period in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue rose 46% to $21 million, from $14.3 million. Net income for 1989 was 
$7.5 million, up 23% from the $6.1 million for 1988. Revenue rose 35%, to $73 
million from $54 million. 
</P>
