<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SELES STOPS SHRIVER IN WASHINGTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monica Seles, who said her hands were shaking, turned back a belated comeback 
bid by Pam Shriver to advance to the semifinals of the Virginia Slims of 
Washington Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Seles won, 6-2, 7-6 (7-5), after holding a 5-2 lead in the second set. 
</P>
<P>
Shriver, who lives in nearby Landover, Md., fought off four match points and 
won four consecutive games to go ahead, 6-5. But Seles, seeded third, then held 
serve at love before winning the final three points of the tiebreaker. 
</P>
<P>
"I was just chickening out," said Seles, who never had played Shriver. "I 
couldn't hit the ball, I was so scared. My hands were shaking." 
</P>
<P>
Today, Seles will Martina Navratilova, who defeated Anne Smith, 6-4, 6-2. 
Navratilova is 19-1 against Smith. 
</P>
<P>
Other quarterfinal winners were Zina Garrison, who beat Nathalie Tauziat of 
Francis, 6-0, 7-6 (7-4), and Natalia Zvereva, who defeated Nicole Provis of 
Australia, 5-7, 6-3, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Petr Korda won 11 of the last 12 points to defeat fourth-seeded Jay Berger, 7-6 
(7-5), 6-1, in the U.S. Pro Indoor at Philadelphia. All of the top six seeded 
players have been eliminated. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Pete Sampras defeated fifth-seeded Tim Mayotte for the third time this 
year, 6-4, 4-6, 6-3; Mark Kratzmann overcame sharp muscle pain to defeat 
eighth-seeded Jim Courier, 4-6, 6-3, 7-6 (9-7); and seventh-seeded Andres Gomez 
served 12 aces to stop Paul Haarhuis, 7-6 (7-3), 6-7 (3-7), 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
It was the seventh victory in as many days for Kratzmann, who had to enter 
through a qualifying tournament. In the semifinals, Sampras will play 
Kratzmann. 
</P>
<P>
Ivan Lendl, ranked No. 1 in the world, beat Patrick Kuenhen of West Germany, 
6-3, 6-3, to reach the semifinals of the ATP Eurocard tournament at Stuttgart, 
West Germany. Boris Becker, seeded second, defeated Miloslav Mecir of 
Czechoslovakia, 6-4, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
