NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arkansas ended Texas' 132-game Southwest Conference winning streak in women's 
basketball by winning, 82-77, at Austin, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
Juliet Jackson made six free throws late in the second half as 25th-ranked 
Arkansas (21-3 overall, 14-1 conference) handed the sixth-ranked Lady Longhorns 
(20-4, 13-1) their first SWC loss since the conference began formal competition 
in 1982. 
</P>
<P>
Texas actually had won 183 consecutive games against SWC opponents dating to 
Jan. 23, 1978, when the Lady Longhorns lost to Texas A&amp;M, 59-52. The league 
didn't sanction women's sports until 1982. 
</P>
<P>
Said Texas coach Jody Conradt: "It hurts, and it's going to hurt more in the 
morning. We have taken pride in the streak. 
</P>
<P>
"If it had to happen, I am glad it happened at home and not on the road where 
we would have felt alone," Conradt said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
