<P>
The Houston Turf Club, spurned in its bid to win a license to build a horse 
racing track in Harris County, filed a $1-billion federal lawsuit against 
several top state officials and private individuals, alleging that they 
conspired to control the potentially lucrative racing industry in Texas. 
</P>
<P>
The suit names more than 20 defendants, including the entire Texas Racing 
Commission, Gov. Bill Clements and Attorney General Jim Mattox. 
</P>
