<TEXT>
<P>
Washington 73, Carson 34 -- Senior guard Detra Lockhart scored 22 points and 
sophomore center Charisse Sampson had 17 points and 23 rebounds to lead the 
top-seeded and defending champion Generals (26-3) past the Colts (22-7). 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 60, Narbonne 43 -- The second-seeded Wolves (22-3) overpowered the 
Gauchos behind 26 points and 17 rebounds from senior center Stacie Toon. Guard 
Tina Means added 18 points. Shasta Paris led Narbonne (18-8) with 13 points and 
10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Poly 61, Lakewood 46 -- Ron Hannibal scored 21 points, including 11 
in the fourth quarter, to lead the Jackrabbits (25-2) in a 5-AA Division 
semifinal at Long Beach City College. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Poly, reaching the final for the first time since 1984, will play 
Lynwood, a 63-60 winner over Santa Monica St. Monica, for the title. 
</P>
<P>
Willie McGinest, Melvin Jones and Yikeen Craddock each added 12 points for 
Poly. Lakewood (18-11), which lost to Poly twice in Moore League play, has been 
eliminated in the semifinals in each of the past four seasons. 
</P>
<P>
Glendora 50, Dominguez 46 -- Randy Rubio scored 14 points and J.J. O'Laughlin, 
an All-Southern Section quarterback who has signed a national letter of intent 
with Illinois, added 12 points as Glendora upset the top-seeded team in the 
field in a 4-AA semifinal game at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
Glendora will play Compton, an 86-73 winner in overtime over Huntington Beach 
Edison, in the final. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Whittiker led Dominguez (23-5) with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
Compton 86, Edison 73 -- James Williams had 30 points and 20 rebounds and 
Darnell Patterson added 20 points as the Tarbabes won in overtime and advanced 
to a Southern Section final for the first time since 1969. 
</P>
<P>
Compton (21-6) will play Glendora in the 4-AA final Thursday at the Bren Center 
at UC Irvine as part of a doubleheader. Artesia will play San Marcos in the 4-A 
final. 
</P>
<P>
Artesia 75, Burbank Burroughs 45 -- All-American forward Ed O'Bannon scored 28 
points as the Pioneers (24-3) won at Cerritos College to advance to the 4-A 
final for the second consecutive year. 
</P>
<P>
Artesia increased a 25-12 lead after the first quarter to a 61-31 margin after 
three quarters. Junior guard DeAndre Austin added 17 points for the Pioneers. 
</P>
<P>
Artesia will play Santa Barbara San Marcos, a 52-39 winner over La Mirada, in 
the final. 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard Santa Clara 70, Tehachapi 58 -- Shon Tarver, a 6-5 senior guard, had 23 
points and 12 rebounds to lead the Saints (23-0) in a 2-AA semifinal at Ventura 
College. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara will play Verbum Dei, an 87-73 winner over Banning, in the 2-AA 
final Saturday morning at the Sports Arena. 
</P>
