<P>
PLAY IN THE SNOW WITHOUT THE COLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although temperatures are expected to reach the 80s today, anyone showing up to 
sunbathe at Craig Regional Park will find sleds racing down the slopes and 
children building snowmen. 
</P>
<P>
More than 100 tons of man-made snow will cover the hillsides from 10 a.m. to 4 
p.m. as the Easter Seal Society holds its annual SnowFest winter carnival 
fund-raiser. There will be toboggan rides, snow-play areas, pony rides, music 
and magic acts. 
</P>
<P>
Admission is $1.50 for adults and 50 cents for children ages 3 to 12. 
</P>
<P>
Parking is $2, with a shuttle service from Brea Mall. Craig Regional Park is at 
3300 State College Blvd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
